The paper focuses on conflict detection and resolution in human-robot interaction, specifically in table top scenarios. This suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the development of the robot's perception and decision-making processes. Additionally, the paper addresses issues of ambiguity and misunderstandings in human-robot interaction, indicating a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of scene perception and object identification also suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
